South Africa’s Biggest Labor Federation Calls for Review of Mining Charter

-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-08-31T11:11:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/south-africa-s-biggest-labor-federation-calls-for-review-of-mining-charter.html
South Africa ’s government must
review the country’s mining charter to ensure the black majority
get a bigger stake in the industry, the Congress of South
African Trade Unions said.  Progress towards increasing black ownership of mines has
been “remarkably poor” and racial transformation of the
industry needs to be accelerated, South Africa’s largest labor
federation said in a written presentation to lawmakers today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
